Citation.sAbstract: A new ionic liquid was chosen for the separation of aromatic hydrocarbons from aliphatic hydrocarbons. The activity coefficients at  infinite dilution, c113 for 29 solutes: alkanes, alkenes, alkynes, cycloalkanes, aromatic hydrocarbons, alcohols, and water in the ionic liquid  1-ethyl-3-methyl-imidazolium thiocyanate [EMIM][SCN] were determined by gas liquid chromatography at the temperatures from  298.15 K to 368.15 K. The values of the partial molar excess enthalpies at infinite dilution DHE;1 1 were calculated from the experimental  c113 values obtained over the temperature range. The selectivities for the hexane/benzene and cyclohexane/benzene separation problems  were calculated from the c113 and compared to the other ionic liquids, NMP and sulfolane, taken from the recent literature. This work  demonstrates that with chosen ionic liquid it is possible to separate different organic compounds with the highest selectivity ever published.
Citation.sTitle: Measurements of activity coefficients at infinite dilution of aromatic  and aliphatic hydrocarbons, alcohols, and water in the new ionic  liquid [EMIM][SCN] using GLC
